# Parent App Design System

## Screen background rule (CRITICAL)

- NEVER set an opaque `backgroundColor` on the outermost `SafeAreaView` or `View` for a parent screen.
- Always use `backgroundColor: 'transparent'` (or omit it) on the screen root.
- The shell gradient is applied by `(parent)/_layout.tsx` via `LinearGradient` at `StyleSheet.absoluteFill` using `GRADIENT_PRESETS` from `theme.store.ts` (light mint / blush / peach variants).
- Inner cards use `backgroundColor: COLORS.parent.surface` = `rgba(255,255,255,0.72)`.

## Text colors

- Primary headings / screen titles: `COLORS.parent.textPrimary` = `#5C3D2E`
- Subtitles / labels: `COLORS.parent.textSecondary` = `#8B6355`
- Meta / hints / muted: `COLORS.parent.textMuted` = `#B89580`
- On blue CTA buttons: `#FFFFFF`
- Shorter alias: `COLORS.parent.text` → same as `textPrimary` (brown on light)

## Primary action buttons

- Main CTAs: prefer `ParentPrimaryButton` from `src/components/parent/ui/ParentPrimaryButton.tsx` using `COLORS.parent.gradientCtaBlue`.
- Secondary outline: `borderColor: COLORS.parent.primary` + `color: COLORS.parent.primary`, transparent fill.

## Cards / surfaces

- `backgroundColor: COLORS.parent.surface` + `borderRadius: 16` + `borderWidth: 1` + `borderColor: COLORS.parent.surfaceBorder`.
- Avoid legacy dark hex fills; `card` / `surface` / `surfaceDark` map to translucent white in `colors.ts`.

## Tab bar (parent layout)

- `COLORS.parent.tabBarBg`, `tabBarBorder`, `tabBarActive` (blue), `tabBarInactive` (muted brown).

## Do NOT

- Do not use solid `#0F0F1A` as the outer screen background in `(parent)`.
- Do not use indigo `#6366F1` as the primary CTA color — `primary` is now blue `#3B82F6` / `gradientCtaBlue`.
